title.narrative: 1.1 PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2025, the Primary Health Care system has increased capacity to deliver integrated and quality maternal and child health, nutrition and wellbeing services, including early detection and interventions for children with disabilities, positive gender socialisation and empower families to demand quality care services., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, all boys and girls from conception to 10 years have access to and utilize quality integrated health, early childhood and education services and families are resilient and empowered to demand quality services in an inclusive care environment.

description.narrative: The Ministry of Health developed a costed Action Plan for the Universal Progressive Home Visiting programme, setting the foundations for sustainable expansion of the home visiting programme Kosovo-wide within the Primary Health Care system. In addition, in support of the COVID-19 vaccination rollout, a National Deployment and Vaccination Plan was developed, a digitalized COVID-19 vaccine registration system was established, vaccination sites were made operational and a risk communication, community engagement and demand generation plan for the take-up of the COVID-19 vaccine was developed. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
